The paper deals with fast Fourier transforms over finite fields, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the associated Lagrange basis, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and the Newton basis, which is a topic in computational algebra (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the construction of subspaces, which is a topic in discrete structures (cs.DS).
